295
00:17:47,291 --> 00:17:49,223
Let's see.

296
00:17:49,291 --> 00:17:53,223
Machiavelli, McCarthy,
Masoch, Miller, Moses...

297
00:17:53,291 --> 00:17:55,813
-Moses?
-Irving Moses, the fruiterer.

298
00:17:55,891 --> 00:17:58,221
Here's Moon. S. Moon.

299
00:17:59,724 --> 00:18:01,587
That's you filed away.

300
00:18:01,657 --> 00:18:04,589
Now then, what would you like to be first?
Prime minister?

301
00:18:04,657 --> 00:18:07,453
Oh, no, I've made that deal already.

302
00:18:07,524 --> 00:18:10,218
I don't know, really.

303
00:18:10,291 --> 00:18:13,223
It's just that I'm not
very good with words.

304
00:18:13,291 --> 00:18:16,654
I didn't have very much
of an education.

305
00:18:16,724 --> 00:18:19,519
And I'm a bit...

306
00:18:22,758 --> 00:18:24,690
I'm just a bit...

307
00:18:24,758 --> 00:18:26,500
Inarticulate.

308
00:18:27,000 --> 00:18:29,182
Yes, that's it. I think.

309
00:18:29,258 --> 00:18:32,690
And you'd like to be the sort of person
who can use words like "inarticulate"?

310
00:18:32,758 --> 00:18:37,316
Yeah! I'd like to be able to talk
to Margaret and tell her how I feel.

311
00:18:37,392 --> 00:18:40,017
An intellectual who can get
his ideas across to the one he loves.

312
00:18:40,091 --> 00:18:42,057
-Yes, that's it.
-Easily done.

313
00:18:42,125 --> 00:18:45,057
Now then, you just stand
over here by the bird,

314
00:18:45,125 --> 00:18:47,784
