1211
01:09:22,196 --> 01:09:25,000
Blow your raspberry.

1212
01:09:26,230 --> 01:09:29,025
I can't, with these terrible fly's lips!

1213
01:09:29,096 --> 01:09:33,256
Quick, blow your raspberry!

1214
01:09:37,330 --> 01:09:39,727
She noticed me, George.
She noticed me.

1215
01:09:40,030 --> 01:09:43,087
I must have her before she goes to
that terrible vice party with the police.

1216
01:09:43,163 --> 01:09:44,921
That's what I'm here for.

1217
01:09:44,961 --> 01:09:46,720
I want her to be in love
with everything about me.

1218
01:09:46,796 --> 01:09:48,270
Madly in love with me!

1219
01:09:48,310 --> 01:09:49,785
Look, Stanley.

1220
01:09:49,863 --> 01:09:53,795
I feel terribly bad about the way
I've tricked you in the past.

1221
01:09:53,863 --> 01:09:58,000
I want to be nice to you this time.
Really nice to you. I mean it. I'd like to help you.

1222
01:09:58,700 --> 01:10:00,788
I've been thinking
about your problem.

1223
01:10:00,863 --> 01:10:03,886
What I think you need
is the simple life.

1224
01:10:03,963 --> 01:10:06,020
How does this strike you?

1225
01:10:06,096 --> 01:10:11,085
You and Margaret
are both warm, tender, loving people.

1226
01:10:11,163 --> 01:10:14,152
Picture a little cottage
in the country.

1227
01:10:14,230 --> 01:10:18,685
Two beautiful children
are playing in the sunlit garden.

1228
01:10:18,763 --> 01:10:21,991
Margaret's in the kitchen,
preparing the anniversary dinner.

1229
01:10:22,063 --> 01:10:24,551
She hears you drive up in the car.

1230
01:10:24,629 --> 01:10:27,118
She's madly in love with you
and you with her.

1231
01:10:27,196 --> 01:10:30,923
She's bursting with the anticipation
of seeing you at the end of the day.

1232
01:10:30,996 --> 01:10:33,985
By George, you've got it.
I think you've got it.

1233
01:10:34,063 --> 01:10:38,552
Julie Andrews.

1234
01:10:38,629 --> 01:10:41,289
Darling!

1235
01:10:46,463 --> 01:10:47,840
Hello, darling.

1236
01:10:47,880 --> 01:10:49,258
Hello, darling.

1237
01:10:49,330 --> 01:10:50,890
Hope you don't mind me
bringing Stanley along.

1238
01:10:50,930 --> 01:10:52,490
Oh, he's always welcome.

1239
01:10:52,562 --> 01:10:54,721
-Would you like a drink, Stanley?
-Please.

1240
01:10:54,796 --> 01:10:57,785
I'll do that. You sit down.
You've been coping with the kids all day.

1241
01:10:57,863 --> 01:11:00,886
Go on. Have a good sit-down. Relax.
What are you going to have? Your usual?

1242
01:11:00,963 --> 01:11:01,937
Yes, dear.

1243
01:11:01,977 --> 01:11:02,952
Right.

1244
01:11:03,030 --> 01:11:05,360
You know that book
I was reading?

1245
01:11:05,430 --> 01:11:08,419
-The Spinoza Reassessment?
-Yes.

1246
01:11:08,497 --> 01:11:11,258
I was thinking Stanley should have
a look at that. Fascinating.

1247
01:11:11,330 --> 01:11:13,795
Absolutely fascinating.

1248
01:11:13,863 --> 01:11:17,590
Here we are. Old Mr. Wine
will soon set you on your feet again.

1249
01:11:17,662 --> 01:11:21,220
-What for you, Stanley?
-Oh, I'll have the same as Margaret.

1250
01:11:21,296 --> 01:11:23,523
Same as Margaret. Wine.

1251
01:11:23,596 --> 01:11:27,256
I bet you thought I'd forgotten
what day it was.

1252
01:11:27,330 --> 01:11:31,500
How awful of me.
I forgot!

1253
01:11:32,000 --> 01:11:34,892
Don't be silly.
You've got so much on your mind.

1254
01:11:34,963 --> 01:11:37,452
Who cares about
a silly old anniversary?

1255
01:11:37,529 --> 01:11:39,500
What matters is
we love each other.

1256
01:11:39,600 --> 01:11:43,553
Do you know, Stanley, we've been married
seven years? It's our wooden wedding.

1257
01:11:43,629 --> 01:11:46,391
Incredible.
I got a little something for you.

1258
01:11:46,800 --> 01:11:48,826
From my heart.

1259
01:11:48,896 --> 01:11:51,124
Darling. Oh.

1260
01:11:53,230 --> 01:11:55,423
Here's to our marriage.

1261
01:11:55,497 --> 01:11:57,724
Here's to all of us.

1262
01:11:57,796 --> 01:11:58,742
Cheers.

1263
01:11:58,782 --> 01:11:59,728
Cheers.

1264
01:11:59,796 --> 01:12:01,785
Cheers.

1265
01:12:01,863 --> 01:12:04,886
I'll go and get that book.

1266
01:12:06,996 --> 01:12:10,485
-I forgot our wedding anniversary.
-Don't be upset.

1267
01:12:10,562 --> 01:12:13,960
-I feel so dreadful!
-Oh, darlingâ

1268
01:12:14,030 --> 01:12:15,504
Here we are.

1269
01:12:15,544 --> 01:12:17,019
See what you make of it.

1270
01:12:17,096 --> 01:12:19,584
We can discuss it at next week's tutorial.
Fine.

1271
01:12:19,662 --> 01:12:22,151
-I must get on with the cooking.
-Don't you do a thing.

1272
01:12:22,230 --> 01:12:26,356
You sit down, relax and enjoy your drink.
I'll do the supper tonight.

1273
01:12:26,430 --> 01:12:29,419
I feel a bit of an intruder,
your anniversary and everything.

1274
01:12:29,497 --> 01:12:32,519
You're not an intruder.
You're very welcome. Isn't he, Margaret?

1275
01:12:32,596 --> 01:12:34,687
Well, I ought to be off anyway.

1276
01:12:34,763 --> 01:12:38,196
I want to catch the Giotto exhibition.
What time's the next bus to Oxford?

1277
01:12:38,263 --> 01:12:41,058
Are you going to that?
I've got a great idea.

1278
01:12:41,130 --> 01:12:44,260
Margaret, why don't you drive Stanley?
You can see it together.

1279
01:12:44,300 --> 01:12:46,860
You've been longing to see that.
It's the last day.

1280
01:12:46,900 --> 01:12:48,960
I can't. There's the supper,
the kids to put to bed.

1281
01:12:49,000 --> 01:12:50,324
I'll do all that.

1282
01:12:50,397 --> 01:12:53,386
It'll be your present to me. Really.

1283
01:12:53,463 --> 01:12:55,395
You are sweet, darling.

1284
01:12:55,463 --> 01:12:57,022
Go on. Enjoy yourself
and come back for supper.

1285
01:12:57,062 --> 01:13:01,860
-Are you sure?
-Absolutely positive.

1286
01:13:01,900 --> 01:13:04,185
Hello, darlings!
Up into Daddy's arms.

1287
01:13:04,263 --> 01:13:05,288
Bye-bye.

1288
01:13:05,328 --> 01:13:06,354
Say bye-bye to Mommy. Bye-bye.

1289
01:13:06,430 --> 01:13:07,904
Look after Daddy, darlings.

1290
01:13:07,944 --> 01:13:09,419
Look after Margaret, Stanley.

1291
01:13:09,497 --> 01:13:11,539
I will.

1292
01:13:11,579 --> 01:13:13,060
Have a good time.

1293
01:13:13,100 --> 01:13:16,219
Blow a kiss to Mommy.
Bye-bye! Bye-bye!

1294
01:13:24,763 --> 01:13:26,487
Do you think he knows?

1295
01:13:26,527 --> 01:13:28,252
It would never occur to him.

1296
01:13:31,330 --> 01:13:33,262
Oh.

1297
01:13:36,430 --> 01:13:38,895
He's such a marvellous man.

1298
01:13:38,963 --> 01:13:43,123
The way he brings philosophy to life.

1299
01:13:43,196 --> 01:13:46,958
Oh, he couldn't be
a better husband or father.

1300
01:13:47,030 --> 01:13:50,621
Or teacher.
He's a saint.

1301
01:13:52,929 --> 01:13:55,191
He's the only man I know

1302
01:13:55,263 --> 01:13:58,058
who actually lives up to his ideals.

1303
01:13:58,130 --> 01:14:00,721
He's such an example to us all.

1304
01:14:04,696 --> 01:14:07,288
The children worship him.

1305
01:14:07,363 --> 01:14:10,386
He's more of a god
than a human being.

1306
01:14:10,463 --> 01:14:13,054
If only he weren't so good.

1307
01:14:13,130 --> 01:14:15,527
If only he had one tiny flaw.

1308
01:14:15,596 --> 01:14:21,224
We must stop thinking about him
and think more of ourselves!

1309
01:14:23,030 --> 01:14:29,900
But it would kill him if he knew.
I feel as if I'm being torn apart.

1310
01:14:34,500 --> 01:14:37,092
My darling.
My precious darling.

1311
01:14:38,996 --> 01:14:41,621
We can'tâ

1312
01:14:41,696 --> 01:14:43,855
We can't keep on denying ourselves.

1313
01:14:43,929 --> 01:14:48,755
All these years we've been married
he's never said a cross word.

1314
01:14:48,829 --> 01:14:54,828
When I was ill
he came to my room

1315
01:14:54,896 --> 01:14:59,561
and he gave me
some soup he had made.

1316
01:14:59,629 --> 01:15:04,324
Oh, Stanley!
How can we do this to him?

1317
01:15:05,430 --> 01:15:07,554
I love you.

1318
01:15:07,629 --> 01:15:10,095
And I love you.

1319
01:15:10,163 --> 01:15:15,152
It can't hurt him
if he doesn't know.

1320
01:15:15,230 --> 01:15:18,128
I wantâ

1321
01:15:18,196 --> 01:15:20,559
I want to give you my love

1322
01:15:20,629 --> 01:15:25,289
in the best,
most beautiful way.

1323
01:15:37,763 --> 01:15:41,423
What? What is it?

1324
01:15:41,497 --> 01:15:44,985
It's his pipe.
His favourite pipe.

1325
01:15:45,063 --> 01:15:47,620
But, Margaret,
don't be upset, please.

1326
01:15:47,696 --> 01:15:49,889
And we were going toâ

1327
01:15:49,963 --> 01:15:52,122
On his favourite pipe!

1328
01:15:54,030 --> 01:15:55,962
The whole thing's impossible!

1329
01:15:56,030 --> 01:15:57,893
-No, Margaret!
-Go. Just go!

1330
01:15:57,963 --> 01:16:00,452
We must never see each other again,
for his sake.

1331
01:16:00,529 --> 01:16:03,825
Margaret, please.
Please, Margaret!

1332
01:16:03,896 --> 01:16:08,794
Margaret, please!
Margaret, I beg of you!

1333
01:16:21,662 --> 01:16:24,026
Hello, Stanley.

1334
01:16:24,096 --> 01:16:26,028
Hold this.

1335
01:16:26,096 --> 01:16:28,028
Whatever you say, George.

1336
01:16:28,096 --> 01:16:30,028
You sound down in the dumps.

1337
01:16:30,096 --> 01:16:31,660
Why not?

1338
01:16:31,700 --> 01:16:35,426
You painted a beautiful dream
and shoved me into a nightmare.

1339
01:16:35,497 --> 01:16:38,724
You should never believe the ads.
Shine the light up a bit.

1340
01:16:38,796 --> 01:16:40,955
What are you doing now?

1341
01:16:41,030 --> 01:16:45,053
Just putting a tiny little
ventilation hole in this oil tanker.

1342
01:16:46,463 --> 01:16:48,894
Up we go.

1343
01:16:50,130 --> 01:16:56,957
That Nicholas was so sickening
with all his blasted sweetness andâ ugh!

1344
01:16:57,030 --> 01:16:59,019
I know what you mean, Stanley.

1345
01:16:59,096 --> 01:17:01,926
Most of the saints throughout history
have been a pain in the neck.

1346
01:17:01,996 --> 01:17:05,224
Give me a hand with these bottles, would you?
I'm due down in Fleet Street.

1347
01:17:05,296 --> 01:17:07,285
You can't stop, can you, eh?

1348
01:17:07,363 --> 01:17:10,056
As a matter of fact, I will very soon.
My job's almost done.

1349
01:17:10,130 --> 01:17:12,062
What do you mean?

1350
01:17:12,130 --> 01:17:15,687
I was up in heaven a few thousand years ago,
having a summit conference with God.

1351
01:17:15,763 --> 01:17:18,093
I was putting forward
a few new proposals.

1352
01:17:18,163 --> 01:17:20,594
-You go up there every now and again?
-Yes.

1353
01:17:20,662 --> 01:17:22,924
We were having a giggle
about Job actually.

1354
01:17:22,996 --> 01:17:27,395
That poor bloke you gave all the boils to
and burnt his home and destroyed his family?

1355
01:17:27,463 --> 01:17:30,560
That's right. God thought
it would be a good idea

1356
01:17:30,600 --> 01:17:33,624
if I tested Job's faith
with a few diseases and disasters.

1357
01:17:33,696 --> 01:17:35,685
You didn't win though, did you?

1358
01:17:35,763 --> 01:17:39,160
In spite of all you did to him,
he still believed that God was good.

1359
01:17:39,200 --> 01:17:42,091
Well, Job was what you'd
technically describe as a loony.

1360
01:17:42,163 --> 01:17:44,958
But as I pointed out
to God at the time

1361
01:17:45,030 --> 01:17:48,757
for every Job or soul
that he lands, I get two.

1362
01:17:48,829 --> 01:17:51,193
I was two billion ahead already.

1363
01:17:51,263 --> 01:17:53,592
You make it sound
like a blooming game.

1364
01:17:53,662 --> 01:17:55,594
That's precisely what it is.

1365
01:17:55,662 --> 01:17:58,992
And the first one to reach
a hundred billion souls is the winner.

1366
01:17:59,063 --> 01:18:03,120
He doesn't stand a chance actually.
I've only got six to go.

1367
01:18:03,196 --> 01:18:05,355
What happens
when you get them?

1368
01:18:05,430 --> 01:18:07,360
Oh, when I've won...

1369
01:18:07,400 --> 01:18:10,660
When I've won the world will be
in such a rotten, stinking mess

1370
01:18:10,700 --> 01:18:12,752
that it can get on
without me.

1371
01:18:12,829 --> 01:18:17,228
I'll go back to heaven, sit on God's
right hand and be his favourite angel again.

1372
01:18:17,296 --> 01:18:22,285
It must be very nice for you to go back
to heaven, but what will happen to me?

1373
01:18:22,363 --> 01:18:25,295
Don't worry, Stanley.
Your future's assured.

1374
01:18:25,363 --> 01:18:27,295
George...

1375
01:18:29,363 --> 01:18:32,090
I don't want to go on
with the rest of my wishes.

1376
01:18:32,163 --> 01:18:35,890
I can't find happiness like this.
You're always too clever for me.

1377
01:18:35,963 --> 01:18:41,457
So I'll be running along
and I'll see you sometime, huh?

1378
01:18:47,400 --> 01:18:50,757
Stanley,
I can't let you go in this mood.

1379
01:18:50,829 --> 01:18:53,886
Let's cancel my appointment.
I'm ahead of schedule, in any case.

1380
01:18:53,963 --> 01:18:57,054
-No, I can't interrupt your work.
-What are friends for?

1381
01:18:57,130 --> 01:19:00,896
I'll round up Avarice and Gluttony,
two lovely girls. The afternoon's on me.

1382
01:19:04,497 --> 01:19:06,985
Oh, eat up, Stanley!

1383
01:19:07,063 --> 01:19:11,000
-Come on, Stanley. Stick one
in Jane Russell and win a goldfish.  -No.

1384
01:19:12,200 --> 01:19:15,958
You have a go, Gluttony.
Chuck 'em. Don't eat 'em.

1385
01:19:16,029 --> 01:19:19,120
This is how Garibaldi lost his life.

1386
01:19:19,196 --> 01:19:23,594
-Enjoying yourself, Stanley?
-You know I can't stand heights, George.

1387
01:19:24,762 --> 01:19:28,354
Up, up, up, up!
Having fun, Stanley?

1388
01:19:31,430 --> 01:19:33,419
Bang!

1389
01:19:35,700 --> 01:19:38,960
-Another 10 shillings gone.
-Don't worry about that, Avarice.

1390
01:19:45,196 --> 01:19:47,424
Enjoying yourself, Stanley?

1391
01:19:48,029 --> 01:19:51,654
That's three pounds-seven and nine pence
without Gluttony's sweets.

1392
01:19:54,200 --> 01:19:55,991
George,
take me out of here, will you?

1393
01:19:58,300 --> 01:20:00,760
Enough, George, is enough.
We didn't need to take a taxi.

1394
01:20:00,800 --> 01:20:03,762
Nothing's too much
for my friend Stanley.

1395
01:20:03,829 --> 01:20:06,989
Thank you very much for this afternoon,
George, but

1396
01:20:07,063 --> 01:20:09,551
I don't think it's really helped,
you know.

1397
01:20:09,500 --> 01:20:11,000
I still don't want to go on with it.

1398
01:20:11,040 --> 01:20:13,060
But you were so nearly there,
last time.

1399
01:20:13,100 --> 01:20:17,052
She loved you, you loved her.
You just left me one little loophole.

1400
01:20:17,129 --> 01:20:20,686
I had to take advantage of it.
Doctor's orders.

1401
01:20:20,762 --> 01:20:25,024
Next time you must specify,
really spell things out in detail.

1402
01:20:25,096 --> 01:20:27,755
I can't think straight anymore.

1403
01:20:27,829 --> 01:20:31,455
Take your time.
Have another lie-down in my room.

1404
01:20:31,529 --> 01:20:35,485
Yeah, and then you put Lust
in the bed just to confuse me.

1405
01:20:35,562 --> 01:20:39,120
I promise you,
Lust won't be there.

1406
01:20:42,762 --> 01:20:44,694
Hello.

1407
01:20:44,762 --> 01:20:47,320
Oh, excuse me. I thought this
was Mr. Spiggott's bedroom.

1408
01:20:47,396 --> 01:20:50,157
How right you were. It is.

1409
01:20:50,230 --> 01:20:54,185
Oh. Well, he must have made a mistake.
He said I could use it.

1410
01:20:54,263 --> 01:20:57,161
Oh, you're his new little favourite,
are you?

1411
01:20:57,230 --> 01:20:59,196
I'm Stanley Moon.
Who are you?

1412
01:20:59,263 --> 01:21:02,161
They call me Envy.

1413
01:21:02,230 --> 01:21:05,025
Not a very attractive name, is it?

1414
01:21:05,096 --> 01:21:09,551
I always wanted to be called Vanity.
Never mind. I'm stuck with it.

1415
01:21:09,629 --> 01:21:12,652
How is Mr. Spiggott these days?

1416
01:21:12,729 --> 01:21:15,423
Quite well.
He may be leaving soon.

1417
01:21:15,797 --> 01:21:17,786
Charming.

1418
01:21:17,862 --> 01:21:20,454
I'm always the last to be told.

1419
01:21:20,530 --> 01:21:23,325
It's funny how he's always
too busy for me

1420
01:21:23,396 --> 01:21:26,987
but he's never too busy
for Lust, ducky.

1421
01:21:27,062 --> 01:21:29,585
He's at her beck and bloody call.

1422
01:21:29,663 --> 01:21:32,720
Look, what are you doing
in George's bedroom?

1423
01:21:32,797 --> 01:21:35,627
Oh, it's"George," is it?

1424
01:21:35,696 --> 01:21:38,093
Good friends, I suppose.

1425
01:21:38,163 --> 01:21:42,323
If you want to know why I'm in his bedroom,
go and take a look at mine.

1426
01:21:42,700 --> 01:21:43,800
What's wrong with it?

1427
01:21:43,840 --> 01:21:44,900
What's right with it?

1428
01:21:44,940 --> 01:21:47,600
For a start, it's half the size
of all the others.

1429
01:21:47,429 --> 01:21:50,691
Wallpaper's peeling off, and it's miles
from the nearest convenience.

1430
01:21:50,763 --> 01:21:54,422
Of course, Lust and Gluttony
are right next door to the bathroom.

1431
01:21:54,496 --> 01:21:56,758
Nothing's too good for them.

1432
01:21:56,829 --> 01:21:59,318
Well, I suppose Lust and Gluttony

1433
01:21:59,396 --> 01:22:02,419
really have to be
rather near the bathroom.

1434
01:22:02,496 --> 01:22:06,053
You're on the seven-wishes bit,
aren't you, dear?

1435
01:22:06,129 --> 01:22:09,789
Yeah, but it doesn't seem
to be doing me much good.

1436
01:22:09,862 --> 01:22:13,625
Although George said if I really specified
the personality, I'd be all right.

1437
01:22:13,696 --> 01:22:16,526
Don't you believe it, cherub.

1438
01:22:16,596 --> 01:22:19,084
He may think he's the cat's whiskers

1439
01:22:19,163 --> 01:22:23,391
but there's one person
who can run rings round him.

1440
01:22:23,463 --> 01:22:25,520
Who do you mean?

1441
01:22:28,000 --> 01:22:29,400
God?

1442
01:22:29,700 --> 01:22:34,456
Old creepy drawers
can't hold a candle to him.

1443
01:22:34,230 --> 01:22:38,322
I think you've got me this time, Stanley.
Let me get it quite clear.

1444
01:22:38,396 --> 01:22:42,328
I want to be a warm, loving,
tender person

1445
01:22:42,396 --> 01:22:45,021
and Margaret exactly the same.

1446
01:22:45,096 --> 01:22:49,085
I want all the fun of meeting her for
the first time and falling in love with her.

1447
01:22:49,163 --> 01:22:52,993
I love her, and she loves me,
we are in love forever.

1448
01:22:53,063 --> 01:22:55,722
Surroundings?

1449
01:22:55,796 --> 01:23:01,660
Serene and far removed
from the false glitter

1450
01:23:01,700 --> 01:23:06,360
the raucous music and the neon lights
of this modern world.

1451
01:23:06,400 --> 01:23:11,526
We are both young, white
and in perfect health.

1452
01:23:11,596 --> 01:23:17,760
Stanley, I've gotta hand it to you.
That's real specifying.

1453
01:23:17,800 --> 01:23:21,853
You've come up with the one formula
that I, as the devil, really dread:

1454
01:23:22,000 --> 01:23:25,000
mutual love
and spiritual values.

1455
01:23:25,500 --> 01:23:32,000
I want peace and quiet
and no other men in her life.

1456
01:23:33,000 --> 01:23:34,700
Julie Andrews.

1457
01:23:40,400 --> 01:23:41,700
Shh!

1458
01:23:44,363 --> 01:23:47,124
Welcome to the Berelian Order, Sister Luna.

1459
01:23:47,196 --> 01:23:50,628
Until you are initiated,
you will wear the habit of a novice.

1460
01:23:50,696 --> 01:23:53,526
We must speak no more.

1461
01:25:48,230 --> 01:25:53,191
The order of the Leaping Berelians
is new and nondenominational.

1462
01:25:53,263 --> 01:25:56,388
Our patron, Beryl of Sussex,
was a simple shepherdess.

1463
01:25:56,463 --> 01:25:59,917
One afternoon she saw a vision
in the sky which beckoned her.

1464
01:25:59,996 --> 01:26:03,019
Dropping her crook,
she leaped towards the vision,

1465
01:26:03,096 --> 01:26:06,584
which, ever receding and ever beckoning,
urged her upwards

1466
01:26:06,662 --> 01:26:09,026
until she disappeared
into the clouds.

1467
01:26:09,096 --> 01:26:11,860
This miracle was witnessed
by a two-year-old child

1468
01:26:11,900 --> 01:26:16,118
who ran to the spot and picked up
Beryl's shoes that had fallen to the Earth.

1469
01:26:16,196 --> 01:26:18,991
That child founded this order

1470
01:26:19,063 --> 01:26:21,620
whose Sisters have taken
a vow of silence

1471
01:26:21,696 --> 01:26:25,026
until such time
as Beryl of Sussex is canonised

1472
01:26:25,096 --> 01:26:29,926
and recognised by the people of the world
for her tremendous feat.

1473
01:26:47,029 --> 01:26:50,961
<i>What is this feeling</i>
<i>that overwhelms me?</i>

1474
01:26:51,029 --> 01:26:53,188
<i>It is something new</i>
<i>and strange.</i>

1475
01:26:53,263 --> 01:26:57,286
<i>It is love, oh, my most cherished.</i>
<i>I see it in your eyes.</i>

1476
01:26:57,363 --> 01:27:02,159
<i>This is love profane. Must be sin in me</i>
<i>that so confounds my senses.</i>

1477
01:27:02,230 --> 01:27:04,957
<i>There is no sin in love, my darling.</i>

1478
01:27:05,029 --> 01:27:07,461
<i>And I love you for all eternity.</i>

1479
01:27:07,529 --> 01:27:10,927
-Margaret.
-<i>You know my name.</i>

1480
01:27:10,996 --> 01:27:12,928
<i>What magic is afoot?</i>

1481
01:27:12,996 --> 01:27:17,122
<i>Our love is written in the book of fate.</i>
<i>There is no escaping it.</i>

1482
01:27:17,196 --> 01:27:19,185
<i>This can't be right</i>

1483
01:27:19,263 --> 01:27:23,661
<i>and yet, within my breast</i>
<i>beats such desire.</i>

1484
01:27:23,729 --> 01:27:26,661
<i>Don't be afraid.</i>
<i>Just trust in me.</i>

1485
01:27:26,729 --> 01:27:29,025
<i>Allow your heart to speak.</i>

1486
01:28:16,200 --> 01:28:19,500
<i>You must go through the initiation ceremony</i>
<i>to show your faith.</i>

1487
01:28:20,000 --> 01:28:21,721
<i>But I'm afraid of heights.</i>

1488
01:28:21,761 --> 01:28:23,986
<i>Show your courage in your leaping.</i>

1489
01:29:47,063 --> 01:29:51,325
I didn't go to vespers.
I had to see if you were all right.

1490
01:29:51,396 --> 01:29:54,362
Oh, Margaret, my precious.
At last we're alone. We can speak.

1491
01:29:54,430 --> 01:29:57,260
But only this once.

1492
01:29:57,330 --> 01:30:00,659
Whatever it is that draws us together
we must cast out.

1493
01:30:00,729 --> 01:30:02,991
It is unnatural and wrong.

1494
01:30:03,063 --> 01:30:06,188
How can it be wrong
if we love each other?

1495
01:30:06,263 --> 01:30:08,229
It is wrong

1496
01:30:08,296 --> 01:30:11,262
and I'm so ashamed to break my vow.

1497
01:30:11,330 --> 01:30:14,557
I came here to find peace and quiet

1498
01:30:14,629 --> 01:30:16,618
and faith.

1499
01:30:16,696 --> 01:30:19,924
-And have you found it?
-Not yet.

1500
01:30:19,996 --> 01:30:25,060
However hard I try
I can't believe that God exists.

1501
01:30:25,100 --> 01:30:27,800
But he does exist.
I know that for certain.

1502
01:30:28,000 --> 01:30:31,321
-How can you be so sure?
-Because I've met the devil.

1503
01:30:31,600 --> 01:30:33,800
-The devil?
-Yeah.

1504
01:30:34,100 --> 01:30:37,827
Let me tell you what happened to me.
I used to be a man.

1505
01:30:37,896 --> 01:30:41,623
My name was Stanley Moon,
and I was a short order cook.

1506
01:30:41,696 --> 01:30:45,094
I was very much in love with you,
but I was too shy to tell you.

1507
01:30:45,163 --> 01:30:47,856
I've never seen you before today.

1508
01:30:47,929 --> 01:30:51,191
I got so miserable
that I tried to kill myself.

1509
01:30:51,263 --> 01:30:54,990
And then George came along
and offered me seven wishes for my soul.

1510
01:30:55,063 --> 01:30:57,824
-Who is George?
-Well, he's the devil.

1511
01:30:57,896 --> 01:31:00,092
We're very good friends.

1512
01:31:00,132 --> 01:31:02,329
He's not so bad
when you understand his problems.

1513
01:31:02,396 --> 01:31:04,362
That's why I keep goingâ

1514
01:31:04,430 --> 01:31:06,362
'Cause I usually disappear
when I goâ

1515
01:31:06,430 --> 01:31:10,453
I find that as hard to believe
as all that about Beryl and her leap.

1516
01:31:10,529 --> 01:31:13,757
But it's true.
And I've got one wish to go.

1517
01:31:13,829 --> 01:31:16,795
I can't think what's happened to George.
Look.

1518
01:31:16,863 --> 01:31:19,022
You see? Nothing.

1519
01:31:19,096 --> 01:31:21,891
I just hope it's not too late.

1520
01:31:23,396 --> 01:31:25,103
I love you, Margaret.

1521
01:31:25,143 --> 01:31:26,850
And I love you, Sister Luna.

1522
01:31:26,929 --> 01:31:30,054
And my love will last forever.

1523
01:31:30,129 --> 01:31:33,526
But it can never be fulfilled.

1524
01:31:36,096 --> 01:31:39,187
I must find George
before he goes to heaven.

1525
01:31:40,263 --> 01:31:42,320
Good evening, Sister.

1526
01:31:53,263 --> 01:31:54,941
We gave already!

1527
01:31:55,200 --> 01:31:56,700
Let me in! Let me in!

1528
01:31:59,729 --> 01:32:02,360
Take that, you great git!

1529
01:32:03,200 --> 01:32:05,000
Sorry, Father.

1530
01:32:07,829 --> 01:32:11,989
Can I be of any help? Oh!

1531
01:32:12,063 --> 01:32:14,154
Wake up, George!

1532
01:32:14,230 --> 01:32:16,695
George, wake up.

1533
01:32:16,762 --> 01:32:19,092
Thank goodness you're still here.

1534
01:32:19,163 --> 01:32:23,788
I was just having
a bit of a nap before the party.

1535
01:32:23,863 --> 01:32:26,761
I've done it.
I've got me hundred billion.

1536
01:32:26,829 --> 01:32:30,360
Oh, congratulations.
Look, what went wrong?

1537
01:32:30,400 --> 01:32:33,293
I blew my raspberry hundreds of times,
and nothing happened.

1538
01:32:33,363 --> 01:32:34,837
I still got
one more wish to go, you know.

1539
01:32:34,877 --> 01:32:36,352
How'd you figure that out?

1540
01:32:36,430 --> 01:32:40,226
I was the intellectual,
I was Sir Stanley Moon, the businessman,

1541
01:32:40,296 --> 01:32:44,319
I was the fly, the pop singer,
the student, and this one makes six.

1542
01:32:44,396 --> 01:32:47,800
What about the Frobisher and Gleason
raspberry-flavoured ice lolly?

1543
01:32:48,200 --> 01:32:50,209
That didn't count!

1544
01:32:50,249 --> 01:32:52,195
Of course it did.
It was a wish, wasn't it?

1545
01:32:52,263 --> 01:32:54,320
That reminds me.

1546
01:32:54,396 --> 01:32:56,385
I owe you sixpence.

1547
01:32:58,296 --> 01:33:00,900
Here we are. Now we're even.

1548
01:33:01,200 --> 01:33:02,660
Then I'm stuck as a woman?

1549
01:33:02,700 --> 01:33:03,900
As a nun.

1550
01:33:04,000 --> 01:33:06,858
You should have specified the sex.

1551
01:33:11,430 --> 01:33:15,521
You've won, haven't you, George?
Well, if I can't have Margaret, I'll kill myself.

1552
01:33:15,596 --> 01:33:18,926
Sorry, Stanley.
It's out of the question.

1553
01:33:18,996 --> 01:33:21,791
Whatever you are on your last wish
you remain forever.

1554
01:33:52,529 --> 01:33:56,155
Isn't this a terrific party?

1555
01:33:56,230 --> 01:34:00,185
Terrific for some, ducky.
Look at the lousy table I've got.

1556
01:34:22,396 --> 01:34:27,259
-Come on, sweetie. Let's dance.
-No, thank you.

1557
01:34:36,396 --> 01:34:39,260
-You're going now, George?
-Yes, Stanley.

1558
01:34:39,800 --> 01:34:43,760
I thought I'd just sneak away quietly.
I don't want to spoil the party.

1559
01:34:44,400 --> 01:34:47,000
Well, I hope you get back in.

1560
01:34:47,300 --> 01:34:49,060
You know, upstairs.

1561
01:34:49,100 --> 01:34:51,120
Thank you very much.

1562
01:34:51,196 --> 01:34:54,525
Apart from Margaret, you're the only
person I've ever enjoyed talking to.

1563
01:34:54,596 --> 01:34:58,926
Now you're going, and...
Well, I can't talk to her.

1564
01:34:58,996 --> 01:35:00,962
I'll rather miss you.

1565
01:35:01,029 --> 01:35:03,359
I'll miss you too, Stanley.

1566
01:35:03,500 --> 01:35:07,759
You know, looking around
the party at everybody

1567
01:35:07,829 --> 01:35:11,625
all of them trying to be something
they weren't in the first place.

1568
01:35:11,696 --> 01:35:15,788
All I want to be is me,
what I was before I met you.

1569
01:35:15,863 --> 01:35:19,955
But that's impossible.
You can't be that without your soul.

1570
01:35:20,300 --> 01:35:24,800
Being me didn't seem like
very much at the time.

1571
01:35:24,900 --> 01:35:29,300
Well, it wasn't very much, but it's
a good deal better than the alternatives.

1572
01:35:31,163 --> 01:35:35,095
I'd give anything to be myself again.

1573
01:35:36,796 --> 01:35:40,711
But I don't have anything to give,
really, do I?

1574
01:35:42,445 --> 01:35:44,434
Look, I'll tell you what, Stanley.

1575
01:35:44,511 --> 01:35:47,307
I've got me hundred billion souls
and a few to spare.

1576
01:35:47,378 --> 01:35:51,300
I don't really need yours.
It's not much of a catch.
I can give it to you back again.

1577
01:35:51,600 --> 01:35:53,473
Is it possible?

1578
01:35:53,700 --> 01:35:57,375
It's never been done before.
It's a very magnanimous gesture.

1579
01:35:57,445 --> 01:36:00,933
In fact, it's a glorious gesture.

1580
01:36:01,200 --> 01:36:03,860
Part of my new image.
Here we are.

1581
01:36:03,900 --> 01:36:05,807
I knew you weren't all bad.

1582
01:36:05,878 --> 01:36:09,060
Of course not. I've just been
thoroughly misunderstood.

1583
01:36:09,200 --> 01:36:11,360
Now, then take this,
burn it up,

1584
01:36:11,400 --> 01:36:14,000
and when it's all gone
you'll be Stanley Moon again.

1585
01:36:14,200 --> 01:36:18,000
Short order chef,
Caucasian, 28, male.

1586
01:36:18,600 --> 01:36:21,600
-And what about Margaret?
-She'll be at Wimpy's as usual.

1587
01:36:21,640 --> 01:36:23,700
Nobody will know
that any of this has ever happened.

1588
01:36:25,200 --> 01:36:27,900
-You're an angel, George.
-Here's hoping.

1589
01:36:27,940 --> 01:36:32,260
Do me a favour, Stanley.
Look after the party for me.
See everybody has a good time.

1590
01:36:32,300 --> 01:36:33,660
When that's done,
it's over to you.

1591
01:36:33,700 --> 01:36:35,500
I'll do my best.

1592
01:36:40,100 --> 01:36:42,875
-Bye, George.
-Bye, Stanley.

1593
01:36:43,800 --> 01:36:48,800
Â§ I'm so good and kind and pretty
I'll be his favourite one again Â§

1594
01:37:07,800 --> 01:37:11,200
-Hello, my good man.
Are you Saint Peter?  -Yes.

1595
01:37:11,240 --> 01:37:13,400
-I'd like to see God, please.
-Who shall I say is calling?

1596
01:37:13,800 --> 01:37:15,860
Oh, come on. You know me.

1597
01:37:15,900 --> 01:37:18,008
Beelzebub, Lucifer, Prince of Darkness.

1598
01:37:18,078 --> 01:37:20,601
-Have you an appointment?
-He's always got time for me.

1599
01:37:20,800 --> 01:37:22,124
I'll just see if he'sâ

1600
01:37:21,700 --> 01:37:25,500
Don't say you'll just see if he's in.
Of course he's in.

1601
01:37:25,540 --> 01:37:27,700
Blimey, how did you get this job?

1602
01:37:28,000 --> 01:37:30,260
-Would you wait here, sir?
-Hurry up then!

1603
01:37:30,900 --> 01:37:34,660
If I were you wanting to get in,
I should try being a bit more humble.

1604
01:37:34,700 --> 01:37:36,860
Oh, would you really? Yes.

1605
01:37:36,900 --> 01:37:39,400
I dare say you would.
You're quite right, of course.

1606
01:37:39,700 --> 01:37:42,300
I'll throw a bit of filth over myself.
That should please him.

1607
01:37:47,800 --> 01:37:51,800
-He'll see you now.
-Oh, thank you very much.

1608
01:37:58,845 --> 01:38:01,072
Hello!

1609
01:38:01,144 --> 01:38:03,474
God!

1610
01:38:03,545 --> 01:38:06,102
It's me.

1611
01:38:06,178 --> 01:38:09,576
Where are you?

1612
01:38:09,645 --> 01:38:13,543
I wish you'd manifest yourself a bit.
It's so hard just talking to thin air.

1613
01:38:13,611 --> 01:38:18,407
On thy belly shalt thou go!

1614
01:38:18,478 --> 01:38:21,205
Oh, blimey. You're not still on
about that, are you?

1615
01:38:21,278 --> 01:38:23,121
All right.

1616
01:38:23,161 --> 01:38:25,005
Dust shalt thou eat!

1617
01:38:25,078 --> 01:38:27,374
Oh, naturally, yes.
Dust, of course. What else?

1618
01:38:27,445 --> 01:38:31,000
Mmm. Delicious.
This is very good. Num, num, num.

1619
01:38:31,200 --> 01:38:32,900
Speak!

1620
01:38:33,400 --> 01:38:36,160
It's a bit difficult
with all this dust in my mouth

1621
01:38:36,200 --> 01:38:38,310
but I've come about readmission.

1622
01:38:38,378 --> 01:38:40,844
You know, I'm ready to
come back in again and join you.

1623
01:38:40,911 --> 01:38:45,367
Hast thou, in thy purpose,
swayed or wavered?

1624
01:38:45,445 --> 01:38:47,741
Swayed or wavered?

1625
01:38:47,812 --> 01:38:51,937
Just take a look at the world.
It's never been in such a mess.

1626
01:38:52,011 --> 01:38:53,860
I've done a wonderful job.

1627
01:38:53,900 --> 01:38:57,273
People are killing each other,
lusting after each other's wives,

1628
01:38:57,344 --> 01:38:59,276
worshipping false idols.

1629
01:38:59,344 --> 01:39:03,743
I've done a marvellous job. It's never been
so sinful, miserable and perverted.

1630
01:39:03,812 --> 01:39:07,437
You should be very happy.

1631
01:39:07,511 --> 01:39:11,170
Oh, don't go forming yourself
into a whirlwind

1632
01:39:11,244 --> 01:39:14,074
just 'cause I got to
a hundred billion souls first.

1633
01:39:14,144 --> 01:39:17,804
Somebody's got to lose. Oh, I'll tell you
something that'll really please you.

1634
01:39:17,878 --> 01:39:21,435
I've done a good deed.
I gave that little twit his soul back.

1635
01:39:21,511 --> 01:39:25,841
Wasn't that generous?
Made me feel marvellous!

1636
01:39:25,911 --> 01:39:28,707
Well, come on. Am I in?

1637
01:39:29,944 --> 01:39:32,900
Hello. Where are you?

1638
01:39:33,500 --> 01:39:34,639
This way, please.

1639
01:39:34,679 --> 01:39:36,341
What's happening?

1640
01:39:36,411 --> 01:39:39,300
One moment he was talking to me,
the next moment he was gone.

1641
01:39:39,600 --> 01:39:42,071
I'm afraid you failed
the entrance examination.

1642
01:39:42,144 --> 01:39:45,508
I can't have failed.
I've done everything he asked of me.

1643
01:39:45,578 --> 01:39:48,339
And to show how repentant I was,
I even did a good deed.

1644
01:39:48,411 --> 01:39:51,844
Made me feel marvellous,
just like I was in the old days.

1645
01:39:51,911 --> 01:39:55,571
There you are. It sounds as if you made
a good gesture for the wrong motives.

1646
01:39:55,645 --> 01:39:57,235
What do you mean,
"wrong motives"?

1647
01:39:57,311 --> 01:40:00,607
For your own joy, to make you
feel better than someone else.

1648
01:40:00,678 --> 01:40:03,905
Oh. Well, I can fix that.

1649
01:40:03,977 --> 01:40:07,637
I'll get Stanley to give me his soul back,
then return it for the right reasons.

1650
01:40:07,712 --> 01:40:10,900
I won't be proud. Tell God not to go away.
I'll be back in a minute.

1651
01:40:17,400 --> 01:40:19,604
Stanley! Hold everything!

1652
01:40:19,678 --> 01:40:22,838
Stanley! Stanley!

1653
01:40:22,911 --> 01:40:27,310
Where are you?
It's me, George, your old friend.

1654
01:40:27,378 --> 01:40:30,160
I want your soul back.
Just for a second.

1655
01:40:30,200 --> 01:40:33,410
Then I'll give it to you back in a better way.
I promise you. Where are you?

1656
01:40:33,478 --> 01:40:35,706
Stanley!

1657
01:40:35,778 --> 01:40:38,869
Are you in there?
It's not a trick.

1658
01:40:38,944 --> 01:40:40,535
Stanley!

1659
01:40:40,611 --> 01:40:43,270
Stanley, wait!

1660
01:40:43,344 --> 01:40:45,300
Stanley!

1661
01:40:59,611 --> 01:41:01,770
<i>I'm gonna do it.</i>

1662
01:41:01,845 --> 01:41:04,333
<i>This time I'm going to do it.</i>

1663
01:41:04,411 --> 01:41:07,605
<i>I've got to do it.</i>
<i>I know I can and I know I will.</i>

1664
01:41:07,700 --> 01:41:11,360
<i>Here I go. Now!</i>

1665
01:41:11,400 --> 01:41:13,157
Miss Spencer!

1666
01:41:13,197 --> 01:41:14,200
What, Stanley?

1667
01:41:17,244 --> 01:41:20,039
I wonder if you'd like to come
and have dinner with me tonight.

1668
01:41:20,111 --> 01:41:23,400
Sorry. I'm already doing something.
Another night perhaps.

1669
01:41:28,278 --> 01:41:33,100
Stanley. Stanley.
She could make it tonight. I could fix it.

